values: It's late~ very late...But darn it all I can't sleep- may be it's excitement? I'm leaving on a trip soon, with Gaara- aaaaaalllll the way to Suna...Good thing most of my students are leaving on vacation of their own- makes closing down the school for a bit that much easier. I haven't been on any trips in awhile...that may explain me being slightly hyper. That and-no offense to Konoha- but a change of scenery might be nice. I'm not even sure if this is making sense- lack of sleep does not fair well with my language skills...

I'm feeling much better ^_^ <small> But that's only because <strike>Nurse</strike> Gaara took care of me ^^</small>

Now I can get back to being my mormal hyper overactive self...YOSH!

Nothing entirely new around here. It's kind of quiet actually...<strike> too quiet </strike>

I need something to do or I'll go crazy...Maybe I'll go visit Gaara, or Naruto, or Hinata, or....somebody.

<lj-cut text="Private to Gaara"> Thursday was fun ^^ <strike> I miss your cooking already <3 </strike> We should do something again soon... </lj-cut text="Private to Gaara">

The silence is driving me crazy...<strike> I guess I'm too hyper for my own good...</strike>

All of the hectic running around has come to and end. I found him and confessed My nerves are humming in excitement and I don't know what to do with all of my excess energy. (Private to Gaara)You have no idea what it was like trying to find you this week- I missed you We can take things at your pace- I don't want to...move too fast for you or anything I guess. (Private to Naruto)Thank you. For talking to me And convincing me to say something to him (I have feelings for you, and I want to be with you. (Gaara and Lee, Saturday night))

I stopped by Gaara's shop today- I saw it was temporarily closed... I'm wondering what's going on...



Lee had stopped by Gaara's shop wondering idly if he could talk to him. He was a bit surprised however to find a sign on the door announcing the place to be temporarily closed. '...Where could he be?' 

Gaara was still pulling tarp over his displays and checking if he left anything else uncovered. He was about to go out when he saw the top of someone's head over his sign. Whoever it was had a bowl cut- and there was only one person who would visit him with that cut. Gaara felt his chest start to tighten. He quickly made his way out the fire escape at the back.

Lee could have sworn he saw movement through the doorway. 'Could he still be in there?' He made his way around to the other side of the building, but he didn't see anything. 'I could have sworn...' 

He was walking quickly. Almost on the verge of running. 'Did he see me? ...I must get to Naruto's dorm.' He turned right into an alley only he and Naruto knew would be a shortcut through the neighborhood. He paused and peeked at the side of the wall. Lee was still looking around the shop area. 'God. I didn't want to see him this early. What with the thing I made Naruto-kun ask him.'

"Oi, where else would Gaara-kun be?" Lee wondered out loud. 'I really need to talk to him too. It's just my luck.' He was about to give up looking around the shop area when he noticed a mop of red hair dart around the corner into an alleyway. 'I may be imagining things but...' "Gaara-kun?" Lee may his way over to the alleyway slowly hoping it was Gaara he saw.

Turn left. Climb up the wall. Jump down. Turn right. Enter a building and leave by the front. Gaara went through the familiar passages until he was finally walking through the park, on his way to the university. He passed through the forested area, just in case. He knew Lee was persistent. He might have followed him even up to there.

Lee had made his way through the alleyway, every time swearing he saw a familar red head dart around the corner but always seeming to miss him. He sighed loudly realizing he had gotten lost with that of the twists and turns he made. 'I'll just find Naruto later and ask if he's seen him...'

Gaara relaxed when he finally entered the campus grounds. He didn't know why he was feeling like this. He didn't want to see Lee- no, he did want to see him. But he felt panic run through him whenever he did. The old feelings were back, though he started to think they never left in the first place. At this point, he didn't want them back. Too many things were at stake, his heart on top of the list.

Lee was more than slightly frustrated when he finally found his way out of the alleyways and into an area he reconized. 'I hope I can find him soon.' The truth was that while he was nervous about talking to Gaara he felt that he needed to. 'Why do things have to be so difficult?'

Things lately have turned the world upside down. 

<strike> Who knew relationships could leave you so confused before they even began?</strike>

So here I am up so late/early, wondering what I can even do---may be I should just let it go for awhile---I don't know.

So I visited Gaara today. It was fun, and we hung out after he left work...Some parts of the evening got awkward I really have to learn to keep my mouth shut








 Lee was once again visiting Gaara at his shop. He had been coming here more often recently. "Ne Gaara, are you free anytime soon?" He asked.

Gaara checked the clock on the desk. "...In a while." He was writing the day's balance in his logbooks. And just like almost everyday this month, Lee was visiting him. 

"Do you want do something?" He walked over to lean on the desk, taking a quick glance at the clock as well.

He looked up from his work to raise a hairless brow at Lee. "What do you plan to do?" 

Lee gave a shrug. "I wasn't quite sure actually, I thought maybe we could think of something together."

 "...Well, we can eat." Gaara checked the clock again and put down his pen with a sigh. "No one's going to buy anything at this time anyway."

"Great!" Lee practically jumped from his spot against the desk. "Anywhere particular you want to go?" 

Gaara winced at Lee's sudden exclamation. He stood up and picked up his sling bag. "You pick." He walked around the desk and headed for the door, knowing that Lee would soon follow.

Lee moved quickly to walk beside Gaara. "Well...I don't normally eat out much- so I don't know many places around here..."

Gaara glanced sideways at Lee. "I'm not picky." He noticed how Lee easily caught up to him, and once again was reminded of their height difference.

" 'I'm not picky'" Lee mocked with a laugh. "Fine fine, first place we spot will be where we eat."

He glared at Lee. "Don't mock me..." He looked around and saw a place with a gold sign hanging from the wall. "There." Gaara pointed with his finger.

"But mocking you is such fun." The comment came out in a teasing tone. Lee looked to where Gaara had pointed. "Alright then! Let's go, I'm hungry!"

Sometimes Lee could be so...insufferable. Gaara sighed and walked next to Lee. When they were standing in front of the restaurant, his face was expressionless. It was a Lebanese restaurant, and on the door was a poster of a bellydancer. "...No."

Lee laughed. "You're the one who spotted it, but we can move on if you want." 

Gaara pushed the door open and stepped in. He wasn't going to back out of their agreement. First restaurant. Damnit. Of all places.... He crossed his arms in front of his chest and glared at the man, asking him where he wanted to sit.

Lee followed Gaara into the restaurant. He noticed Gaara glaring at the waiter and quickly told him it was only two and a seat anywhere was fine before the poor man lost some limbs. 

Gaara followed the waiter who was holding up his tray onto his chest. They were led to a semi-circle couch lined with carpets and fake furs. In the middle was a small bronze table. Gaara sat on the other side of the couch and looked at the menu the nervous waiter handed to him.

Lee sat opposite of Gaara, taking the other menu from the waiter before watching him dart off. "I think you scared the poor man Gaara." Lee stared blankly at the menu before setting it aside.

"Heh." Gaara glanced at the list on the menu. There was a translation on the side. "...Where's that waiter? Have him order for us."

Lee glanced around the restaurant, but he couldn't spot the man that seated them. He spotted a different waiter and called him over instead.

 Gaara fixed his gaze on the waiter and said, "Get me something good." He held out the menu and promptly ignored the waiter. He didn't think he needed to expound.

Lee chuckled at the expression the waiter held. "I'll have what ever you decide to bring him." He handed the menu back with a polite smile.

Leaning back against the furs, Gaara looked at all the bronze items and paintings decorating the restaurant. The different shapes made his fingers twitch. He wanted to carve those figures in his glass art.

Lee had leaned forward and now had and elbow on the table and his chin resting on his palm. He saw Gaara's eyes flicker over the walls- more than likely looking at the decorations. "They would look better in glass." 

He looked at Lee, leaning on the table. "Aa." He sank down onto the furs and waited for their food to arrive.

Lee had grown used to the pauses in conversation with Gaara, the silence more of a comfort than a moment of awkwardness. He took this moment to scan the restaurant again, taking note of all the bronze in the place. 'Don't the know about any other metals?' Lee found himself thinking. 

Suddenly, kaballah music started to play from the speakers. Gaara started from his slouch and looked at Lee as if he was the one playing it. Then he noticed the other guests start to clap their hands. "What?"

Lee sat up his attention now focused on what could be going on. "Gaara...do you have any idea as to what is happening right now?"

Gaara shook his head, eyes widening when a scantily clad woman suddenly came out from the back of the restaurant. He glared at her as she passed by them. Then he turned to Lee. "Where's our food?"

"I-I don't know." Well the poster on the door made much more sense now. 'And this had to be the first restaurant why?' That thought swam in his head until the waiter finally came back with their food.

Gaara picked up a stick with what looked like chicken speared on it. He started to bite it. Then he stiffened, turned his head and narrowed his eyes at the dancing woman who had caressed his hair.

Lee almost choked on the bite of- whatever it was on the stick when he saw the glare resurfaced on Gaara's face. He couldn't help it if Gaara glaring was amusing when it wasn't you as the glare's target, but it would help to swallow his food before trying to laugh or comment on it.

He turned his glare towards Lee who he saw was choking. He just knew he was laughing at him. He resumed his assault on his stick, his patience wearing thin.

Lee had managed to swallow properly after a moment. "Maybe it would be best to finish here quickly so you don't turn everyone to stone with your glares ne Gaara?" Lee's lips stretched into an amused grin.

Gaara just continued eating, ignoring Lee for the moment. The food was good...at least by his standards. He shifted his foot a bit, brushing against something. He paused, blinked, then reached for another stick.

Lee paused in the middle of chewing his food when he felt something brush against his leg- he mentally shrugged before he swallowed 
heavily and grabbed another stick. The actual restaurant may be odd, but at least the food tasted good.

As soon as Gaara finished his stick, he drank the sweet honey drink provided by the restaurant. Then he said, "Now what?" He couldn't help it, he wanted to get out of the place fast. 

Lee finished up quickly as well and called the waiter over for the bill. "Well, first we get out of here. Then we worry about what's next."

Gaara took out his wallet, intent on paying for half the bill. 

"Ah, Gaara I've got it." Lee pulled out his own wallet while gesturing for Gaara to put his away.

Gaara didn't budge. "Lee, I can pay for myself."

"Ah I know...I guess I just wanted to treat you is all." He was rubbing the back of his head now, nervous laughter following his sentence.

Lee's nervous laughter made him look at Lee. Then he nodded. "I'll pay you back another time." Gaara thought, 'Lee must be securing his own 'treat' in the future. How practical.'

Lee was about to explain that he really expect- nor need- to be paid back, but he figured it was a conversation better suited for another time. He carefully tucked the correct payment, along with a tip, into the bill folder the waiter left on the table. He then moved out of his side of the booth and waited for Gaara to do the same.

Gaara followed Lee out of the booth and out of the restaurant. He slung his bag around his shoulders. He looked at Lee and said, "Lee, you have sauce on your mouth." He leaned over and wiped it off with his hand. Then took a tissue he took from their table and wiped his hand clean.

"Thanks." A light blush rose on Lee's cheeks. 'Ah, why am I blushing.' The thought only made Lee turn a darker shade of red. "Uh, so what now?"

Gaara didn't see Lee's blush, already moving to walk down the street. "...You decide." Really, Lee was the one who wanted to 'hang out' as they call it, with him. He should decide where they would go next.

 "This probably sounds stupid- but do you want to see a movie? I mean if you don't want to that's fine..." The whole sentence had come out awkward and unsure- something Lee never expected of himself. 'Just what exactly has me so flustered today?'

 A movie? Well, there was supposed to be a really good movie showing right now...Gaara turned around. "Okay. But nothing weird."

Lee nodded in agreement. "Nothing weird gotcha--wait...what exactly constitutes as weird for you?" 

Gaara eyed Lee. "...Aliens. And those stupid movies where 30 year old women act as 13 year old girls."

"Alright then! No aliens and 30 year olds with teenage complexes." Lee gave Gaara a thumbs up and a smile- the classic "good-guy" pose.

Gaara looked at the thumb jerked upwards before dismissing it. He was shown that pose too many times, although it still made him want to 
rub his head in annoyance. 

"So what are we standing around here for anyway?" Lee turned toward the direction of the local cinema and started walking. 

Gaara followed Lee, glancing sideways every now and then. He was glad Lee didn't tire of their companionship. Even after all these years.
 
"Ne Gaara, mind if I ask you something?" 

"...Sure." He turned his head to look at Lee.

"You don't have to really answer, I'm just curious- but are you interested in anyone?" Lee looked at Gaara out of the corner of his eye. "I mean romantically..."

He stopped walking, turning his head quickly to glance at Lee. "What?" He felt his chest tighten again. Unlike in college, he knew that it was a signal he was getting flustered. 

"Are you interested in anyone romantically?---You don't have to answer, I shouldn't have asked...I mean, never mind." Lee didn't even know why he asked that stupid question in the first place.

He didn't know how to answer that. He couldn't answer that. He turned back towards the path. "...I'll tell you another time." He started walking again. Unknown to him, the tip of his ears were pink.

Lee followed behind Gaara a bit and took notice of the pink tint to the tips of Gaara's ears- wait was Gaara blushing. 'Can a pink tint to the top of the ears even be considered blushing?' As Lee pondered the wonderment and many levels of blushing he didn't notice that he and once again caught up to Gaara.
